Until recently, several states, including Germany, were against making these nominal documents available to the public because of the sensitive nature of some information.
What is the alleged homosexuality or mental disability of some victims of deportation?
The registers of concentration camps or arrest warrants compiled by the Gestapo were collected after the war for the practical purpose of finding deported or forced labour by civilians, bringing them proof of their incarceration in order to open the way for their compensation.
Even today, more than 300 permanent employees in Bad Arolsen deal with tens of thousands of individual applications.
