In addition, the number of systems for the execution of transactions with financial instruments is being expanded by joining regulated secondary markets with multilateral trading systems and order internalisation systems that will compete with current exchange brokers.
The law also requires investment services companies to disseminate information on the market on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and ways to cope with risk, and requires that they keep a record of all operations performed to simplify supervision by the CNMV.
During a hearing in the Congressional Trade Commission, several adjustments were included, among which stands out that securitised receivables were considered to be a "complex" financial instrument given the high risk to the investor, which was demonstrated by what occurred in the U.S. with high-risk mortgages.
In addition, the transposition of the Directive was used to legally outline the functions that bachelors in economics and business management can hold for 30 years after a Royal Decree was approved in 1977, which outlines professional functions reserved for economists.
At the same time, the Senate has included the creation of new professions in the financial sector, such as an intermediary who will work externally, will not require permission from the CNMV and will be able to provide product trading and client acquisition services for various investment firms at the same time.
