What insurance is suitable for me?
Insurance of a car that protects the driver in the event of an accident. represents a significant expense, which depends on various factors such as age, condition, sex, length of possession of the driver's license, the type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to clarify what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insurer.
This obligation takes the form of an insurance contract, which provides that the insurance company will receive the agreed amount of insurance in a certain amount for taking care of the payment of damages in the event of an insurance event.
Insurance is the price of insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors such as age, condition, sex, length of possession of the driver's license, type of vehicle insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies determine their prices on the basis of statistics, so the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both individuals over the age of 25 and women need to pay lower insurance, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
Similarly, on the basis of inspections, insurance companies have concluded that married persons have fewer accidents than self-employed drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of driving, and thus the likelihood that it will have an accident.
With increasing frequency of rides, the likelihood increases.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when determining the price of insurance.
Therefore, the driver must carefully study the situation in order to choose the insurance that best matches his insured profile.
We will show here the most important variables for choosing this or that type of insurance, which in addition to being suitable for the type of insurer, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of twenty-five face a variety of disadvantages such as little driving experience and short possession of a driver’s license when they want to negotiate insurance at an affordable price.
Although insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are also cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks with an insurance discount so that they get insurance coverage for all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would involve the participation of the client in the payment of the insurance event.
"The part of the insurance event reimbursement provided by the client will be predetermined in determining the price of the insurance, which will be the higher, the lower the participation," explains Luis Noguera, chief executive of First Europe in Spain, an Internet insurance broker.
Another option is insurance extended to other participants in the operation so that the client insures against damage caused to other people, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, it would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
Recommendations.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce your insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the insurance company has.
On the other hand, malus is an increase in the above-mentioned basic rate.
"Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus," Noguera explains.
After crossing the 25-year limit, drivers find it easier to take out insurance, as the client’s risk index decreases, thanks to the experience they have gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to take out insurance against all risks with a discount.
"Young people are usually not able to take advantage of the pre-acquired experience at the time of the accident, not even while driving," assures the director of the European company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of the procedure, when the "fear of a newcomer" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to take out insurance against all risks, if, of course, his economic situation allows.
Families with children are considered to be clients with the lowest risk index and therefore their premiums will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with an insurance discount (which could be 300 euros) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other participants in the operation, starting the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
"Their driving is quieter and their purchasing power is higher, so they can afford to get the highest discount," notes Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are advised to take out insurance against all risks with an insurance discount (which is 150 euros) or insurance extended to other participants in the operation, if a high bonus has been achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a considerable expense, which is a good reason to properly study the insurance options that would be most suitable for us in view of our personal situation.
